 in Ontario.&nbsp;</p><p>This scholarship is offered to students who are permanent residents of Canada and wish to study anywhere in Ontario. The scholarship rewards excellence in high school studies. It provides financial assistance for undergraduate studies at any public college or university in the Province of Ontario, including the University of Toronto.</p><p><strong>Scholarship Amount</strong>: This scholarship varies upon academic standing.</p><p><strong>Eligibility criteria for The Ontario Trillium Scholarship</strong>: To be considered, you must meet the following requirements:</p><ul><li>You must have attended secondary school in Ontario</li><li>Your academic standing must be the highest possible</li></ul><h3><strong>7. The George Brown College Entrance Awards</strong></h3><p>The Government of Ontario offers this scholarship is open to Bangladeshi students who wish to study in any field at George Brown College.</p><p>This is another scholarship in Canada for Bangladeshi students. The Government of Ontario offers this scholarship is open to Bangladeshi students who wish to study in any field at George Brown College.</p><p><strong>Scholarship Amount</strong>: This scholarship ranges from $1000 to $5000 per year (for a maximum of two years)&nbsp; for study in any field at George Brown College.</p><p><strong>Eligibility criteria for The George Brown College Entrance Awards</strong>: To be considered, you must meet the following requirements:</p><ul><li>You must have attended secondary school in Ontario</li><li>Your academic standing should be excellent</li></ul><h3><strong>8. Ontario Student Assistance Program Scholarships</strong></h3><p>This program offers scholarships to students from low-income families in Ontario.</p><p>This program offers scholarships to students from low-income families in Ontario. The scholarship rewards excellence in high school studies and provides financial assistance to undergraduate study at any college or university in the Province of Ontario, including the University of Toronto.</p><p><strong>Scholarship Amount</strong>: This scholarship is offered based on financial need, academic standing, and the course you wish to study</p><p><strong>Eligibility criteria for Ontario Student Assistance Program Scholarships</strong>: To be considered, you must meet the following requirements:</p><ul><li>Your family’s income must be below $70,000 a year</li><li>You must have attended secondary school in Ontario*</li><li>Your academic standing should be excellent</li></ul><p>Please visit their<a href=\"https://osap.gov.on.ca/OSAPPortal\"> Website</a> for further information.</p><h3><strong>9. Bangladeshi Community Scholarship for Academic Excellence, Canada</strong></h3><p>This scholarship is offered to students who are permanent residents of Canada and wish to study in any field at the University of Toronto.</p><p>This scholarship is offered to students who are permanent residents of Canada and wish to study in any field at the University of Toronto. This scholarship rewards excellence in high school studies and offers financial assistance for undergraduate study at any college or university in the Province of Ontario, including the University of Toronto.</p><p><strong>Scholarship Amount:</strong> The scholarship varies based on academic standing.</p><p>Eligibility crit<strong>eria for Bangladeshi Community Scholarship for Academic Excellence, Canada:</strong> To be considered, you must meet the following requirements:</p><ul><li>You must have attended secondary school in Ontario</li><li>Your family’s income must be below $70,000 a year</li><li>Academic standing should be excellent*</li></ul><p>Please visit their<a href=\"https://aoscottawa.org/programs-services/\"> Website</a> for further information.</p>', 'canada-scholarship-opportunities-for-bangladeshi-students-2022', 'admin/image/blog/thumbnail/blog_1658996458_976106.png', 1, '2022-07-28 18:20:59', '2022-07-28 18:20:59');
