(4, 'Complete Guide to Co-op Programs for International Students', 'Complete Guide to Co-op Programs for International Students', 'Cooperative education is referred to as a co-op program. It is a distinct degree from traditional academic studies. In a co-op program, a student works in an', 'Complete Guide to Co-op Programs for International Students', NULL, 0, '<h4><strong>Introduction</strong></h4><p>Cooperative education is referred to as a co-op program. It is a distinct degree from traditional academic studies. In a co-op program, a student works in an area similar to the course he is taking and receives firsthand experience with his profession once he completes his degree.</p><p>For example, Lincoln University offers cooperative education or co-op at both the undergraduate and graduate levels. Co-op is a paid work term that people can undertake while studying. With industry leaders like Honda or IBM, students can earn anywhere from $14 to $30 per hour.</p><p><strong>How does co-op help to boost both education and career?</strong></p><p>Students obtain a lot of knowledge about their field. A co-op program might be a great way to supplement students’ education. If they’re considering doing co-op, then they will get the following advantages:</p><ul><li>&nbsp;</li><li>As co-op students, they get compensated for their job and have the opportunity to network with employers and create valuable connections.</li><li>Students can learn more about their possible careers and see if they like them. Also, they can get away from the classroom for a while.</li><li>Students improve their interviewing and resume-building skills dramatically.</li></ul><p><strong>Eligibility for co-op studies for international students</strong></p><p>Work experience is part of the curriculum in some study programs. Besides, if students meet the following criteria, they can apply for a co-op or intern work permit:</p><ul><li>Students have to have a valid study permit.</li><li>Work is required to complete a student’s study program in Canada.</li><li>Students must have a letter from their school confirming that all students in their program must complete work placements to graduate</li><li>Students’ co-op or internship accounts for 50% or less of their study time.</li></ul><p><strong>General requirements for co-op studies&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>Before applying, students must have completed two semesters of study.</li><li>Have a GPA of 2.0 or higher.</li><li>Before students begin their applications, they have to take the one-credit co-op preparatory course (this requirement does not apply to graduate students).</li><li>If students are law students or undergraduate students, they must have the correct pattern of attendance (POA) to use careers.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements for co-op studies for international students</strong></p><p>International students must satisfy the following conditions before beginning their co-op after accepting an offer:</p><ul><li>Attend an information session on Curricular Practical Training (CPT) for overseas students interested in co-op. CPT is a permit that allows international students to participate in co-op, internship, practicum, clinical, and corporate residency programs. Attending this class is critical because the entire process of obtaining CPT may be more challenging than you anticipated.</li><li>One of the topics discussed in the session could be that if students work for more than 12 months on CPT, they risk losing their Optional Practical Training (OPT), which allows them to work in the United States after graduation. So, if they’re thinking of attending a Co-op, they shouldn’t forget to check out the OGS event calendar to see when and how students may register.</li></ul><p><strong>Types of co-ops</strong></p><p>During studies, students can do one of the three types of co-ops listed below:</p><ol><li>6 months full-time (January to June or July to December)</li><li>4 months full-time (Summer, Fall, or Spring)</li><li>20 hours per week part-time + courses (Summer, Fall, or Spring)</li></ol><p><strong>The application process for international students</strong></p><p>The step-by-step application process for co-op studies for international students is given below:</p><ol><li><strong>Schedule a meeting with the co-op coordinator</strong>: Students have to talk to them about their career interests and aspirations; this will help them recommend Co-op possibilities that are right for that student. Through Career Counselor Appointments, students can schedule appointments with their department’s Co-op coordinator.</li><li><strong>Make a resume or a portfolio</strong>: The first thing students need for their co-op application is a strong résumé. They can and should seek resume writing assistance from their co-op advisors. They routinely interact with and speak with both companies and students to better understand what businesses are looking for and what talents or abilities students possess that they might not consider including on a resume. Student’s academic advisors can also assist them, particularly with technical jargon expressing industry-specific talents. VMock, an online resume-review tool that employs language processing and machine learning to deliver fast, individualized comments on their resume based on criteria obtained from employers and resumes from other Northeastern students, is also available for free.&nbsp;</li></ol><p>Students need to create a husky account, upload a PDF version of their resume, and wait a few minutes to receive specific comments on how to improve their resume to match what employers are looking for.</p><p>Some organizations want cover letters, portfolios, or samples of students’ work, usually submitted in PDF format. If Students have a WordPress blog or their website, they shouldn’t be afraid to link to it in their resume.</p><ul><li><strong>Students can use NUcareers, Northeastern’s job, and co-op application portal, to upload their resumes and cover letter.</strong></li></ul><ol><li><strong>Using NUCareers to apply:</strong> The Cooperative Education dashboard is accessible through NUcareers’ Cooperative Education link. Students can use this page to browse for employment and events and post their CVs and cover letters. NUcareers has put together how-to articles, video tutorials, and FAQs to assist students with their co-op search. Have more concerns? Inquire with your co-op coordinator.</li></ol><p><strong>Conclusion</strong></p><p>Studying a CO-OP program in Canada will open doors in the job market in ways not possible in other countries. Not only because it is a conventional disruptive training style but also because it provides teaching and the opportunity to study and experience the topic students will be focusing on.</p>', 'complete-guide-to-co-op-programs-for-international-students', 'admin/image/blog/thumbnail/blog_1658996662_353921.png', 1, '2022-07-28 18:24:23', '2022-07-28 18:24:23'),
(5, 'Selecting the Best Student Loan to Study Abroad for International Studentsï¿¼', 'Selecting the Best Student Loan to Study Abroad for International Studentsï¿¼', 'Education loan plays a vital role in the lives of deserving students who desire to study in a renowned institutionâ€”many students step back to fulfill this', 'Selecting the Best Student Loan to Study Abroad for International Studentsï¿¼', NULL, 0, '<h4><strong>Introduction</strong></h4><p>Education loan plays a vital role in the lives of deserving students who desire to study in a renowned institution—many students step back to fulfill this dream due to their financial problems. But with education loans, things have become relatively more straightforward for parents to send their children and for students to pursue their higher education abroad. Some factors need to be kept in mind before thinking about studying in abroad. These factors are competitive interest rates, more extended moratorium periods, flexible repayment terms, eligibility, documents, etc. So before reaching any conclusion few things must be considered to proceed with an efficient education loan.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>What is a student loan, and how does finance studying abroad?</strong></p><p>Student loans are loans that are provided for those students who aspire to study abroad but find it difficult to arrange funds. These loans are funds that you have to pay back. They work like any other loan, with a few changes. You can get a student loan from the government or a private bank. This bank can be from your home country or a foreign bank, o the country you wish to pursue your studies. . Education loan has become a popular choice because of its flexibility. Quality education at global universities is now conceivable with an easy education loan.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Types and benefits of student loan</strong></p><p>Several types of education loans are available for students, such as co-signing. Parents or legal tutors are very general for private student loans as most teenagers don’t carry the credit history to get a loan to such an extent. However, student loans that you can develop from the government are inclined to be more promising, as the rates are generally lesser. Some loans are grounded on financial need, whereas others are much like any other loan and are grounded on the credit score.</p><p><strong>Some benefits that student loans offer</strong></p><ul><li>Competitive interest rates</li><li>Pre-approval before the confirmation of admission</li><li>Up to 100% finance</li><li>Some of the other expenditures that a loan covers include equipment purchases, charges for the hostel, and additional costs related to the course.</li><li>Door to door services</li></ul><p><strong>Eligibility&nbsp;</strong></p><p>The things that are examined while providing a student loan are:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Student profile: Academic background, co-curricular involvement, scored in tests like GRE, TOEFL, work experience, and more</li><li>Guardian’s profile: Financial background, personal properties, yearly income. Current standing loans, sources of revenue, etc.</li><li>Recognized University: Ranking of the university, acceptance rate, notable alumni, reputation, and more&nbsp;</li><li>Norms of lenders: This depends on the terms and conditions of the organization that you are requesting your loan.</li></ul><p><strong>What student loans covers&nbsp;</strong></p><p>Student loans may be flexible for paying tuition, accommodation, transportation, books, materials, facility fees, and various expenses. The loan may also cover equipment such as computers or hostel, or dorm necessities.</p><p>So basically, a student loan can cover&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Tuition</li><li>Rooms and board</li><li>Fees</li><li>Study abroad trips</li><li>Book and supplies</li><li>Equipment</li><li>Travel costs&nbsp;</li></ul><p><strong>Some steps and concerning factors that need to be known for studying abroad&nbsp;</strong></p><p>Education loans for abroad studies should always ensemble an applicant’s need, and specialists say that besides your financial state, several other factors such as nation, university, course, and length, rate of interest amongst others, should be kept in mind while before accommodating an offer.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Interest Rate</li></ul><p>Interest rate remains the foremost vital calculation to be considered, whereas selecting a bank for an education loan since, indeed a tiny distinction, can cost you spend a substantial sum of cash. You must understand the difference between fixed and floating rates of interest, relate interest rates offered by various banks and financial institutions, and go for the most profitable option.</p><ul><li>Eligibility and Documents&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Most banks and monetary teachers have an assessment handle to decide your qualification of the advance. The method incorporates an intensive survey of your academic background, credit value, co-applicant subtle elements, family pay etc. Also, not all financiers extend financial aid for all courses, so checking your eligibility in advance is suggested.</p><ul><li>Moratorium Extension&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Lending banks and money lenders provide a grace period of six months to one year after completing the course. Sometime recently, the prepayment began, known as the moratorium—typically done to provide students time to procure work and jobs and gain economic stability before paying back their education loans.</p><ul><li>Prepayment Terms</li></ul><p>The sooner you pay back the credit, the more you save on the interest that collects on your initial sum. Inquire on the off chance that your lender will charge a penalty on prepayment. Depending on that, you can plan to get a work to repay the loan as long as you’re able.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Loan Processing Time&nbsp;</li></ul><p>When you apply to abroad universities, meeting the deadline is crucial. The loan sanction letter is a vital report required to appear as verification of financial assets at the time of university and visa application. It is critical to inquire about the credit handling time of different loan specialists to assist you to arrange your total application handle accordingly.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Total Cost over EMI</li></ul><p>Education credit is reimbursed in EMIs and distributed equitably through the loan residency. A few individuals lean toward more extended loan residencies to bring down the month-to-month installment sum. Go with the loan specialist who offers you the most acceptable interest rate amid an advanced residency that produces your bundle cost-effective.</p>', 'selecting-the-best-student-loan-to-study-abroad-for-international-studentsi', 'admin/image/blog/thumbnail/blog_1658996758_879454.png', 1, '2022-07-28 18:25:59', '2022-07-28 18:25:59'),
(6, 'What Type of MBA is suitable for students in Canada?', 'What Type of MBA is suitable for students in Canada?', 'Canada offers limitless chances in practically any sector, thanks to its state-of-the-art educational infrastructure, top-notch teachers, opportunities for', 'What Type of MBA is suitable for students in Canada?', NULL, 0, '<h4><strong>Introduction</strong></h4><p>Canada offers limitless chances in practically any sector, thanks to its state-of-the-art educational infrastructure, top-notch teachers, opportunities for international exposure, and world-renowned colleges for Management courses. Management courses in Canada, such as the MBA, have obtained international certification and give students a platform to improve their managerial talents through industrial projects. In addition, low living costs, modest tuition prices, and low crime rates have made Canada a popular destination for overseas MBA students.</p><p><strong>How Is MBA in Canada Lucrative?</strong></p><p>MBA is a significant financial investment in your future. It teaches students more than how to read a spreadsheet or lead a group. An MBA program can open the door to new experiences and opportunities. That is precisely what MBA programs in Canada do. Universities such as Queen’s, McGill, Rotman, and the University of Canada West provide programs that allow students to hone their skills in dealing with real-world business problems.</p><p>There are numerous reasons to choose Canada as your MBA study abroad destination. Furthermore, choosing an MBA from a country with a thriving economy and a demand for highly educated people ensures solid career opportunities in Canada following graduation. However, there may be a few additional aspects students want to think about before selecting. Here are a few pointers that may be useful to you:</p><p><strong>Qualification with International Recognition: </strong>A degree from Canada will be recognized internationally, just like a degree, diploma, or certificate from the United States or the United Kingdom.</p><p><strong>Cultural Diversity: </strong>Several ethnic groups exist in Canadian society. This multicultural civilization allows students to interact with people from all over the world, making students more capable of working alongside and even leading diverse cultural groupings.</p><p><strong>Immigration is simple: </strong>Obtaining a Canadian Student Visa is simple, and students can even seek permanent residency after completing their degree.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Possibilities &amp; Opportunities: </strong>Academics are valued highly in Canadian business schools, and students have various opportunities to demonstrate their inventiveness and other skills.</p><p><strong>Types Of MBA Being Offered in Canada</strong></p><p><strong>Full-Time</strong></p><p>The MBA is one of the most well-known and distinguished degrees in Canada and worldwide. Full-time MBA programs are available at Canadian universities to help students build the abilities needed to advance into management positions.</p><p>IN CANADA, full-time MBA graduates receive a general management degree that teaches them how firms operate and how business executives adapt to ever-changing issues. Finance, marketing, strategy, human resources, and operations management are all covered in the full-time MBA program. A full-time MBA from Canada is internationally recognized.</p><p><strong>Part-Time&nbsp;</strong></p><p>Most MBA programs in Canada provide one or two weekend classes to students. On the other hand, a part-time MBA allows students to work full-time while studying.</p><p>It takes three to five years to complete a part-time MBA degree in Canada. The difference in fees is not considered because it covers the same content as the full-time MBA program (only over a longer time).</p><p>Students will gain a broad understanding of critical business functional areas and their interconnections as part of the program, which will help them develop business skills.</p><p><strong>Executive</strong></p><p>The Executive MBA is a practice-oriented graduate business degree developed for working executives at the highest levels. The EMBA’s emphasis on group learning through peer exchange and collaborative teamwork is one of its most distinctive qualities. It allows working professionals to share their experiences, learn more, and expand their horizons.</p><p>Students can apply for an EMBA program in Canada if students have at least 5 to 7 years of relevant experience. In Canada, GMAT scores are not required to pursue an EMBA. In Canada, students can work while studying for an EMBA.</p><p><strong>Dual Certification</strong></p><p>Joining a Dual Degree MBA program in Canada is a fantastic method to receive an MBA education. Many MBA universities in Canada offer Dual Degree MBA programs specifically created for students who desire to earn an MBA while also earning a second supplementary degree.</p><p>A student can earn both an MBA and a graduate degree in engineering, medical, science, law, education, or technology through a Dual Degree MBA program.</p><p><strong>Top Universities with Best courses offered in Canada for MBA</strong></p><p><strong>Rotman School of Management&nbsp;</strong></p><p>The Rotman School of Management at the University of Toronto is regarded as one of the best business schools in the world. The university is known for creating expert business managers and is ranked 54th among the best global universities for MBA. Its management school offers five different MBA programs, including a full-time 2-year MBA, part-time MBA, Executive MBA, and other specialty programs. The university is known for its research, internships, and multicultural learning environment.</p><p><strong>University of McGill</strong></p><p>McGill University’s Desautels Faculty of Management offers an MBA program ranked first in Canada and 48th worldwide. Students can finish a full-time 1-year MBA in 16, 20, or 28 months in part-time mode at the university, which offers excellent flexibility in course duration.</p><p><strong>Ivey Business School</strong></p><p>The Ivey Business School of the University of Western Ontario is known worldwide for its excellent placement record and offers one of the best MBA programs in Canada. The business school features a rigorous 1-year MBA program appropriate for people who want to learn industry-specific abilities in less time to train themselves for a professional career, with two out of every five alumni holding top management positions.</p><p><strong>Smith Business School</strong></p><p>Queen’s university has a solid reputation when it comes to high-quality education. Among Canadian institutes, the university has the best career outcomes. The Smith School of Business offers four MBA programs, including one full-time one-year MBA and three executive and specialized MBA programs.</p><p><strong>Schulich Business School</strong></p><p>York University’s Schulich School of Business is notable in Toronto, offering the most varied MBA courses in Canada with various specialties. Accounting, Artificial Intelligence, Business Analytics, Finance, and Supply Chain Management are some of the specialties available in the course.</p><p><strong>Other Important MBA Universities in Canada</strong></p><p>Professional teaching staff offers the best MBA courses to a varied student body at universities across Canada. Here is a list of other Canadian universities that offer MBA programs.</p><ul><li>University of Dalhousie</li><li>Guelph University (Guelph)</li><li>Windsor University</li><li>Regina’s University</li><li>University of Thompson Rivers</li><li>Victoria University</li><li>University of Brock</li><li>University of Vancouver Island</li><li>University of Trinity Western</li><li>University of Cape Breton</li><li>New Brunswick University</li></ul><p><strong>Conclusion</strong></p><p>The financial services sector grew by 11.6 percent over the last decade, resulting in more job prospects for MBA graduates. MBA is one of the most sought-after occupations in Canada. MBA jobs in Canada can pay anywhere from 80,000 to 200,000 dollars per year. EY, Accenture, and Amazon are among the top recruiters for MBA grads. Another element that makes an MBA in Canada a popular choice is the straightforward Post Work Permit. More than 600,000 study permits are issued each year.</p>', 'what-type-of-mba-is-suitable-for-students-in-canada', 'admin/image/blog/thumbnail/blog_1658997241_716730.png', 1, '2022-07-28 18:34:01', '2022-07-28 18:34:01'),
(7, 'Why Homestay is the Best Accommodation for International Students', 'Why Homestay is the Best Accommodation for International Students', 'Are students excited to start their study abroad adventure yet worried about living in a homestay? Don&#039;t be concerned! We recognize that staying with a', 'Why Homestay is the Best Accommodation for International Students', NULL, 0, '<h4><strong>Introduction</strong></h4><p>Are students excited to start their study abroad adventure yet worried about living in a homestay? Don’t be concerned! We recognize that staying with a foreign family is not the same as staying at home. Even if students need to adjust to the environment, homesickness, culture, and customs, there are many reasons to be excited about homestay housing. While there may be a lot to consider when selecting homestay lodging, we are here to assist students in their search for their next home.</p><p><strong>Homestay</strong></p><p>Described, a homestay is a portion of someone’s home converted into lodging for visitors for a fee. The host, generally a local family, primarily provides overnight accommodations in their home for tourists. Still, the homestay owners may also offer additional services such as meals, local travel arrangements, pickups, and more. A homestay is less daunting for first-time travelers than large, impersonal hotels. Even for frequent travelers who are constantly on the move, a homestay is a terrific opportunity to meet new people and experience a ‘home away from home atmosphere. Nowadays, many individuals prefer homestays since the hosts’ services are more personalized and cheaper.</p><p><strong>5 Reasons Why Homestays are Better</strong></p><ol><li><strong>Students are save</strong></li></ol><p>When students and parents consider studying abroad, they frequently have safety concerns. If students choose homestay as their abroad accommodation, students can rest confident that our homestay partners carefully select host families. While students explore their new surroundings and life as international students, this gives their parents peace of mind. If students are not used to living away from home, a homestay can be an excellent option because students will always have someone to look after them. Having someone to ask, “How was your day?” having dinner together as a family and spending time with your overseas friends can also help ease the transition to life abroad.</p><ol><li><strong>Students can quickly increase their language skills</strong></li></ol><p>Students will be exposed to various people, cultures, foods, and languages during your homestay. You’ll be a part of honest conversations and quickly pick up on local terminology every day. Your language and culture will be of interest to the host families. It might begin with students celebrating your country’s festivals, holidays, and special occasions while also learning about theirs! Learning about local customs and visiting tourist places with your host family can be fun to learn about their culture.</p><ol><li><strong>Students don’t miss home as much</strong></li></ol><p>Even the most self-sufficient travelers can get lonesome. Festivals, birthdays, and family dinners in your nation may be missed. Your host family can be pretty supportive during these times and may even spend time with students at a local restaurant enjoying supper to help take your mind off being homesick.</p><ol><li><strong>Students gain independence</strong></li></ol><p>Staying with a host family does not imply a lack of independence. Some students are hesitant to choose a homestay because they believe they will not have the freedom they desire or be placed with a strict host family. On the other hand, host parents understand that students want to see the city while you’re there. Because communication is crucial in everything, just let them know ahead of time if you’re going out, staying with a friend, or arriving home late. Students will not only retain a positive relationship with their host family, but students will also be able to go on their adventures during their stay abroad if students do so. In this way, homestay strikes the ideal mix between independence and having someone look after you.</p><ol><li><strong>Students will be able to save more money</strong></li></ol><p>One of the most appealing aspects of homestay is the cost. A homestay is a fantastic option because it provides much more than just a roof over your head, including safety, cultural experiences, guidance, utility services, and certain meals – all for a fair price! This means you’ll have more money to spend on excursions, activities, and weekend vacations.</p><p><strong>Benefits of Homestay</strong></p><p><strong>Meet the locals</strong></p><p>When students stay in a homestay, students get to do something students won’t get anywhere else: not only do students meet the locals, but students also get to live with them. It’s a means of experiencing a destination rather than just visiting it.</p><p><strong>Money well spent</strong></p><p>Many of our hosts provide incredible weekly and monthly savings to individuals searching for longer-term accommodations. Homestays are highly cost-effective. In Dublin, hosts offer double rooms for less than €30 per night. Others in Manhattan’s core offer rooms that start at €55 per night. Travelers to Australia’s beautiful Gold Coast may get a double hotel for as little as €34 per night.</p><p><strong>Transferring to a new city</strong></p><p>Moving to a new location is both terrifying and thrilling. When students first arrive, you’re in foreign territory, and it takes some time to adjust. Stay at a homestay, and you’ll meet some local folks right away, in their home, who will soon make students feel more at ease, secure, and at ease in your new location.</p><p><strong>Take a supper together.</strong></p><p>Our hosts are encouraged to add a complimentary light breakfast to the accommodation rate (some homestays can provide other meals too by prior arrangement). The best part is that you’ll share a dinner with your hosts and learn firsthand about the region and local culture.</p><p><strong>Ideal for single travelers</strong></p><p>While traveling the world is a fantastic experience, there’s something comfortable about staying with someone who knows the area well when students arrive. You’ll meet interesting people, share tales and experiences, and learn about the place through the eyes of the locals when students stay in a homestay. Traveling alone may be a freeing experience, and some would say that it is the ideal way to travel.</p><p><strong>Conclusion</strong></p><p>A homestay is something students should do at least once because it allows students to see the place through the eyes of a native. You’ll fall in love with the notion of living in a homestay because of the personalized experiences it provides. Stay with family students like and choose homestays correctly for your next holiday, and you’ll never be homesick!</p>', 'why-homestay-is-the-best-accommodation-for-international-students', 'admin/image/blog/thumbnail/blog_1658997352_289254.png', 1, '2022-07-28 18:35:53', '2022-07-28 18:35:53'),
(8, 'Your Complete Guide to Applying for Colleges in Canada', 'Your Complete Guide to Applying for Colleges in Canada', 'The number of international students in Canada increased by 68 percent between 2014 and 2018. In 2018, 721,205 international students studied in Canada, the', 'Your Complete Guide to Applying for Colleges in Canada', NULL, 0, '<h4><strong>Introduction</strong></h4><p>The number of international students in Canada increased by 68 percent between 2014 and 2018. In 2018, 721,205 international students studied in Canada, the most ever. Canada had nearly 622,000 international students as of 31 December. Its global student population was almost 640,000 in 2019 before the pandemic lowered it to 530,000 international students in 2020.</p><p>There are innumerable opportunities for students to pursue higher education in Canada, and many of the world’s top universities are located there. Accept a diverse and multicultural environment, live in a safe country with a high quality of life; universities focus on research, and many applaud their groundbreaking discoveries; learn more about why the Canadian teaching style is so effective.</p><p><strong>Eligibility Guide to Applying for Colleges in Canada:</strong></p><p>Thus, every university in Canada has its own admissions requirements and will evaluate individually. However, secondary school graduation and good academic standing are generally the minimum standards for undergraduate courses.</p><p><strong>Find a course and apply to universities.</strong></p><p>When applying to a university in Canada, individuals will select and apply for a specific major, but this is more flexible in the UK if applicants change their minds. To obtain a student visa, visitors must apply to an institution on the designated learning institutes (DLI) list and be sure about what they want to study at the universities they have chosen, as there are separate fees for each program and university apply to.</p><p><strong>What documentation is required?</strong></p><p>Official documents, such as transcripts from secondary or postsecondary schools may be required. These records may need to be evaluated and translated into English or French. For more data on extent acknowledgment, contact your country’s educational authorities or the Canadian Information Centre for International Credentials (cicic.ca).</p><p><strong>Do you have the required language skills?</strong></p><p>Depending on the university, international students in Canada must demonstrate proficiency in either English or French. Many English-language universities require applicants to have a certain level of proficiency on a standardized language test. French-language universities typically evaluate applicants on an individual basis.</p><p>If one’s language skills are inadequate, there are various Canadian programs available before actually trying to apply to a college in the country offered by universities, colleges, and private institutions.</p><p><strong>What is the procedure for applying to study in Canada?</strong></p><p>The application process varies by province. Understudies in some areas can apply through a centralized application service. In some cases, applicants must apply directly to the university. Some applicants may wish to apply to more than one program or university if their first choice is not accepted.</p><p><strong>Top universities in Canada that should be considered for study abroad adventure:</strong></p><ul><li>University of British Columbia</li><li>Thompson Rivers University</li><li>University of Winnipeg</li><li>Humber College</li><li>University of Toronto</li><li>York University</li><li>University of Manitoba</li></ul>', 'your-complete-guide-to-applying-for-colleges-in-canada', 'admin/image/blog/thumbnail/blog_1658997483_25190.png', 1, '2022-07-28 18:38:04', '2022-07-28 18:38:04'),
(9, 'A Complete Guide to Australia&#039;s VETASSESS Assessment', 'A Complete Guide to Australia&#039;s VETASSESS Assessment', 'VETASSESS is an Australian government-approved skills assessment agency that evaluates the applications of numerous professionals seeking to move to Australia', 'A Complete Guide to Australia’s VETASSESS Assessment', NULL, 0, '<h4><strong>What is VETASSESS?</strong></h4><p>VETASSESS is an Australian government-approved skills assessment agency that evaluates the applications of numerous professionals seeking to move to Australia on Skilled Visas. It’s Australia’s leading vocational education and training assessment provider that provides skills assessments for General Professional Occupations and Trade Occupations. VETASSESS is experienced in evaluating job applicants’ qualifications and work experience, migrants, students, and industry members. Authorized VETASSESS staff assess and authenticate that the applicant’s qualifications, job experience, and duties they claimed to be skilled at professionally for immigration purposes meet the Australian Government’s standards for the linked nominated occupations.<br><br><strong>Why is VETASSESS required?</strong></p><ul><li>Having a VETASSESS skill assessment is a must to be eligible for applying for a Skilled VISA.</li><li>It verifies that the applicant is a genuinely skilled individual with the necessary qualifications in his field.</li><li>The applicant’s points test system may award him additional points based on the positive assessment result.</li></ul><p>There are <i><strong>two types of VETASSESS skills assessments </strong></i>available to applicants:-</p><ul><li><i><strong>VETASSESS Professional Occupations – Skills Assessment Type-1</strong></i></li></ul><p>This includes evaluating the applicant’s qualifications and employment of the suitability of his nominated occupation and assessing the level of qualification’s comparability with the Australian Qualifications Framework (AQF). The assessment includes determining whether the applicant’s employment location is within or outside of Australia and making decisions about the relevance of their work experience and qualifications for the nominated occupation.</p><p><i><strong>Application process</strong></i></p><p>First, applicants must determine whether the occupation they require the skill assessment is on the list of skilled jobs. There are six groups of professions.</p><p>Group A&nbsp;</p><p>Group B</p><p>Group C</p><p>Group D</p><p>Group E</p><p>Group F</p><p>Different groups have different qualification requirements and standards. They must apply for the evaluation following their particular group’s standards.</p><p><i><strong>VETASSESS Professional Occupation Skills Assessment Applications – Processing Time</strong></i></p><p>The length of time it takes to process Professional occupations skills assessment applications is determined by the type of application. It usually takes between 8 and 10 weeks.</p><ul><li><i><strong>VETASSESS Trade Occupations – Skills Assessment (Type 2)</strong></i></li></ul><p>VETASSESS created a fact sheet with varied criteria for various jobs. The VETASSESS trade professions skills assessment compares the applicant’s abilities and knowledge to your specified occupation as outlined in the VETASSESS fact sheet. Your qualifications and occupational license will be evaluated against approved Australian and non-Australian qualifications and occupational licenses.</p><p><i><strong>Application process</strong></i></p><p><strong>Pathway 1</strong> – If the applicant doesn’t have an Australian qualification or occupational license, he’ll need to take this route.</p><p>The minimum work experience requirements for the chosen profession:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>6years of experience in a licensed trade (with no formal training).</li><li>4 years of experience in a licensed trade (with relevant formal training).</li><li>5 years of experience in non-licensed trades (with no formal training).</li><li>3 years of experience in non-licensed trades (with relevant formal training).</li></ul><p>Applicants must show proof of full-time paid employment in their chosen profession. Employer statements and payment records are essential documentation (pay slips, bank statements, taxation records, annual payment summaries, etc.) A copy of the applicant’s qualification must be sent (Award certificates and Transcripts).</p><p><strong>Pathway 2</strong> – If the Applicants hold an Australian qualification or occupational license, pathway two it is.&nbsp;</p><p>For the applicant’s specified occupation, the following minimum Australian qualifications or current Australian occupational license and work experience criteria apply:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>A copy of the applicant’s Australian qualification or current Australian occupational license must be submitted.&nbsp;</li><li>Applicant must show proof of three years of full-time paid employment in his specified occupation at a suitable skill level.&nbsp;</li><li>Pay stubs, bank statements, tax records, annual payment summaries, and other documents may be included.&nbsp;</li><li>Applicants having a current Australian occupational license must show that they have worked full-time in the nominated occupation in Australia for at least 12 months in the previous three years.</li></ul><p><i><strong>VETASSESS Trade Occupation Skills Assessment Applications – Processing Time</strong></i></p><p>The length of time it takes to process trade occupation skills assessment applications is determined by the type of application. It usually takes between 12 and 14 weeks.</p><p><strong>&nbsp;Necessary Documents</strong></p><p>All documents must be colored copies of the originals in good quality. If your documents aren’t in English, you’ll need to submit copies of the sources and English translations from a licensed translator.&nbsp;</p><ul><li><i>Processing Fee</i></li><li><i>Photograph</i></li><li><i>Identification proof</i></li><li>Primary Identity Documents<ul><li>Passport bio-page scan</li><li>Birth certificate&nbsp;</li></ul></li><li>Secondary Identity Documents</li><li>National ID</li><li>Driver’s License</li><li>Social security card</li><li>Marriage certificate</li><li>Student identity card</li><li>Australian visa grant</li><li><i>Change of name&nbsp;</i></li><li><i>&nbsp;Proof of qualification</i></li><li>Degree certificates&nbsp;</li><li>Transcripts</li><li><i>Proof of employment</i></li><li><i>&nbsp;</i>Employer reference letter</li><li>Payment Evidence – e.g., Payslips, Bank Statements, Taxation Documents, insurance or superannuation records, etc.</li><li>Organizational Chart (In case of Managerial Occupations)</li></ul><p><strong>General Tips:</strong></p><ol><li>Choosing a suitable occupation for a skills evaluation can be challenging.</li><li>Applicants must be aware of their job category and their place within it. Despite being the norm in their home country, the applicants’ qualifications and methods of performing the job may differ from those used in Australian sectors. The Australian and New Zealand Standard Classification of Occupations evaluates job roles.</li><li>Don’t be discouraged if the applicant does not meet all of the job requirements. He might have other choices. Determine where the candidate excels in terms of Australian occupational norms.</li><li>The applicant’s major field of study may be extremely relevant in some job sectors.</li><li>Confirm the applicant’s primary job responsibilities.</li><li>Verify that the applicant’s work experience is highly relevant.</li><li>Please verify that the applicant can demonstrate his seniority.</li><li>Applicants will need a mix of qualifications and work experience.</li><li>If the applicant is self-employed, he must provide documentation.</li></ol>', 'a-complete-guide-to-australias-vetassess-assessment', 'admin/image/blog/thumbnail/blog_1658997606_66684.png', 1, '2022-07-28 18:40:06', '2022-07-28 18:40:06'),
(10, 'All You Need to Know About TSS 482 Visa', 'All You Need to Know About TSS 482 Visa', 'The elaborated form of the TSS visa is a temporary skill shortage visa. In Australia, the term TSS 482 visa demonstrates that superiors can underwrite', 'All You Need to Know About TSS 482 Visa', NULL, 0, '<h4><strong>Introduction</strong></h4><p>The elaborated form of the TSS visa is a temporary skill shortage visa. In Australia, the term TSS 482 visa demonstrates that superiors can underwrite individuals from remote areas for employment in their business. However, this visa is for a short-term period and can be accorded the visa up to 4 years. The TSS visa allows foreign nationals to live in Australia while working full-time in the proposed status. The applicants for the TSS visa may mention the dependent family members in the application. Additionally, there are no age restrictions for the TSS visa. However, there are restrictions only for permanent residency.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>To make a student’s TSS 482 visa acceptable:</strong>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>On the combined skilled occupation list, a student must have a similar profession as per the occupation list.&nbsp;</li><li>The employer must choose an employee to recruit for work for a particular job position.&nbsp;</li><li>A relevant skill and qualification are required</li><li>&nbsp;per a student’s profession.&nbsp;</li><li>Two years of work experience is mandatory in a student’s professional life.&nbsp;</li><li>A student’s English Language ability must be fluent.&nbsp;</li><li>Good character and health are required for fulfilling DHA requirements.&nbsp;</li><li>A student should have a substantive visa or a bridging visa A, B, or C and have assembled with the visa condition given if the student is in Australia.&nbsp;</li></ul><p><strong>There are some requirements to achieve this TSS 482 visa.</strong>&nbsp;</p><p>The international students who are sponsored by their superiors to work in the businesses in Australia are required to:</p><ul><li>Foreign nationals should legitimately employ the&nbsp;</li></ul><p>company.</p><ul><li>A foreign national should not have inauspicious information in opposition to the business.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>A particular job should be proposed to the foreign nationals that they work for full time and genuinely.&nbsp;</li><li>Correlated to the requirements, an employer should fulfill foreign nationals’ salary and employment conditions.&nbsp;</li><li>If necessary, a foreign national should verify Labour Market Testing.</li></ul><p><strong>In total, there are seven steps to apply for this TSS 482 visa:&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li>As per the integrated <strong>skilled occupation list,</strong> an applicant should inspect whether the applicant’s profession is mentioned or not on the list.&nbsp;</li><li>An applicant should make sure that they have fulfilled all the requirements to apply for a TSS 482 visa.</li><li>Proficiency in the English Language.</li><li>While staying in Australia, an applicant should have health insurance.&nbsp;</li><li>In Australia, all visa applicants should have health and character checks as per the requirements.&nbsp;</li><li>An employer can take the application online through the Department of Home Affairs (DHA); the applicant is required to search for an employer who is obliged to sponsor the applicant for employment in Australia.</li><li>An applicant should receive a proposal from an employer.</li></ul><p>Once an applicant successfully finds an employer, the applicant’s first responsibility is to make the employer propose the applicant for the TSS visa. The employers can complete the appointment online through the DHA. When the applicants are simultaneously applying for the TSS visa, the employer can register the application by designating and sponsoring the applicant.&nbsp;</p><p>The applicant should apply for the TSS visa.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Once the employer has submitted the&nbsp;</li></ul><p>delegation visa, an applicant can apply for the visa online through the DHA.</p><ul><li>An applicant should wait for the employer’s resolution.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Deciding an applicant’s visa might take several months for the DHA. In 2018, the processing time used to take 11-18 days for the TSS visa.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>The applicant should receive their visa and begin to work.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>Once the application has met authorization, the applicant should receive their visa and begin to work.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>The benefits that this TSS visa holds:</strong>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>In Australia, an applicant can also apply for permanent residency. However, the applicant’s employer must subsidize through Employer Nomination Scheme (186) or Regional Migration Scheme (187).</li><li>When employers struggle to accumulate skilled Australian employees, the TSS 482 visa empowers the employers to convey qualified employees to reduce human resource insufficiencies.&nbsp;</li><li>The TSS visa holders can do employment in Australia and lead to permanent residency as per the proposed status.</li></ul>', 'all-you-need-to-know-about-tss-482-visa', 'admin/image/blog/thumbnail/blog_1658997798_590866.png', 1, '2022-07-28 18:43:19', '2022-07-28 18:43:19');
